wn course successfully, Anne offers her daughter advice intended to help her negotiate the difficult passage of a woman in the world of politics. This is the first translation into English of Anne of France's Lessons.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian lifevEarly works to 1800. 0aConduct of lifevEarly works to 1800. 4aMedieval History. 4aMedieval Literature. 4aWomen's & Gender Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Feminist.2bisacsh  a15th Century.  aAnne of France.  aLessons.  aPolitical Guidance.  aPrincess.  aWomen in Politics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846152658423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846152658/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles